[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: E, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 0, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "79dd3098553afc8ecb322e74fdc915fb4d3028f0ec130c30d2dba5a76d6fb00c"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/stayman"]
[Student "S"]
{East opens 1NT.  

With 11 points and a 4-card Major suit you bid 2\C. Partner answers 2\S. What is your next bid? 

Stayman bidding can be very straightforward. Partner has 4 \Ss, you have 4 \Ss. That makes 8. Partner has 15-17 points, you have 11-12 points. That makes 26-29.

You bid 4\S.}

